T1  - Oophoropexy to the Round Ligament after Recurrent Adnexal Torsion.
T2  - Ooforopexia ao ligamento redondo em um caso de torcao anexial recorrente.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1055/s-0038-1673426
A1  - Goncalves, Ines Sarmento
A1  - Sampaio, Joana
A1  - Felix, Joana
A1  - Silva, Ana Catarina
A1  - Fornelos, Gisela
A1  - Silva, Pedro Tiago
Y1  - 2018//
Y2  - 20181011//
N2  - Recurrent adnexal torsion is a rare gynecological emergency. We report a case of recurrent ipsilateral adnexal torsion in a woman with polycystic ovaries, previously submitted to a laparoscopic plication of the utero-ovarian ligament. Due to the recurrence after the plication of the utero-ovarian ligament, the authors performed a laparoscopic oophoropexy to the round ligament, which is an underreported procedure. The patient was asymptomatic for 1 year, after which she had a new recurrence and needed a unilateral laparoscopic adnexectomy. Since then, she regained the quality of life without any gynecological symptoms.Oophoropexy to the round ligament may be considered when other techniques fail or, perhaps, as a first option in selected cases of adnexal torsion, as it may allow the prevention of recurrence without increasing morbidity while preserving the adnexa. Copyright Thieme Revinter Publicacoes Ltda Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
